        "testata": "France 24",
        "lingua_originale": "en",
        "titolo_orig": "Mojtaba Khamenei as Iran's new Supreme Leader signals continuity to international community",
        "testo_it": "Iran: Mojtaba Khamenei designato come nuovo leader supremo, segnale di continuità politica.",
        "priorita": "Alta",
        "id_gruppo": 2,
        "link": "https://www.france24.com/en/mojtaba-khamenei-as-iran-s-new-supreme-leader-signals-continuity-to-international-community",
        "orario": "12:06",
        "timestamp": 1773313608,
        "contenuto_esteso": "To display this content from YouTube, you must enable advertisement tracking and audience measurement. One of your browser extensions seems to be blocking the video player from loading. To watch this content, you may need to disable it on this site. Mojtaba Khamenei as Iran's new Supreme Leader signals continuity to international community Middle East Issued on: 12/03/2026 - 12:06 Modified: 12/03/2026 - 12:40 Amid the political uncertainty surrounding Mojtaba Khamenei, Iran's new Supreme Leader, Nadia Massih is pleased to welcome Dr Anahita Motazed Rad, Visiting Senior Fellow at the London School of Economics. As the Islamic Republic navigates a moment of acute pressure, the elevation of Mojtaba Khamenei serves an important political function, explains Dr Motazed Rad. By maintaining him as the formal leader, the regime sends a message to both domestic elites and the international community that institutional cohesion remains intact during a time of war. Middle East war: Oil tankers set ablaze in the Gulf in latest Iranian attacks 12/03/2026 Middle East US war on Iran: 'An American war in desperate search of a strategy', expert says 12/03/2026 Middle East Banking, finance and consultancy firms evacuate staff in Gulf States 11/03/2026 Middle East 'Two decades in the making': Expert details how Mossad built its spy network in Iran 11/03/2026 Middle East US war on Iran: Using military force to achieve political outcomes rarely produces lasting stability 11/03/2026 Middle East Israel launches new 'large-scale' wave of strikes on south Beirut 11/03/2026 Middle East Iran may tap into organised crime to carry out terror attacks, expert says 11/03/2026 Middle East Citi, StanChart evacuate Dubai offices, HSBC closes Qatar branches as fears grow 11/03/2026 Middle East 'US war on Iran tactically very successful: Strategic success will be 'elusive', warns Schneiderman 11/03/2026 Middle East"
